  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Misuse of nadi remedies",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Achiruvan has died due to the treatment given to a 15-year-old boy suffering from blood cancer under the guise of pulse therapy.",
        "According to investigations, the boy's family from Vavunia relied on the pulse treatment of a person in Urumbrai and stayed in Vattukkottai area of \u200b\u200bJaffna for treatment.",
        "A 15-year-old boy from Vavunia died on Monday (18) at a house in Vattukkottai.",
        "After that, the Vattukkottai police, who carried out investigations, recovered the body and handed it over to the Jaffna Teaching Hospital for post-mortem examination.",
        "In this case, during the sudden death investigation, the parents informed that the boy was treated at Urumbarai.",
        "While there is a special medicine for blood cancer, the boy's parents were convinced that nadi treatment is better.",
        "The report of the Sudden Death Investigation Officer and the Forensic Medical Officer will be presented in the Mallagam Magistrate's Court."
      ],
